conscientious, responsible), D (takes responsibility seriously), A (anticipates danger, leadership), C (calm, correct decisions). Technical competence: A (spatial vision, complex connections), B (weather assessment, computer), C (understands complicated tech), D (problem solving). Calmness under pressure: B (handles stress), C (keeps calm in crisis), D (responds adequately), A unknown. Decision-making: C (quick correct decisions), A (anticipates dangerous situations), B (weather assessment), D (problem solving). Teamwork/communication: A (leadership but unfriendly, not open), B (pretentious, wrong tone), C (concern for others but communication difficulty, egocentric), D (loner, hot temper). Professional development: B (computer skills, but weak memory for numbers), C not willing to further education, D maybe okay, A not open to new ideas.\n\nThus B seems strongest overall, with only communication tone issue. C has caring but communication difficulty and egocentric. A has leadership but unfriendly and not open. D has responsibility but hot temper and loner.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate B.\n\nUncertainties: How severe are B's communication issues? Could they affect crew safety? Could any other candidate have hidden strengths in teamwork? Need more data on A's crew interaction beyond leadership, D's ability to work with crew despite hot temper, C's ability to overcome communication issues.\n\nWhat would change vote: evidence that another candidate has strong teamwork/communication that outweighs B's issues, or evidence that B's communication issues are minor.\n\nNow produce public message and metadata."}
